    "body": "Yes; if the main file has a signature or some other kind of identifier, it’d be preferable if it was displayed first on blockchain explorers when you verify the contract.  \r\nAlso it improves readability of the contract if libraries are listed in an order that makes sense for the particular contract.  \r\n\r\nWhen troubleshooting this originally, I was hoping that I could specify the order using the `solidity` configuration in `hardhat.config.ts` but I couldn’t make sense of the solidity documentation and/or how it affected hardhat’s output of the contracts. Could there be a way to set it there?",
